content.description: Starts on the low angle slabs.  350 feet of .7/8 slab climbing will get you to the vegetated ledge below the “thumb”. Climb the thumb and find the two piton anchor and get up there!
content.protection: Double set of cams to 3 Camalot
content.location: In the drainage after passing whale dome, hike for 25 minutes and stash gear next to a giant boulder below the slabs.   Head straight up and you will see the start. Few options for the start all below .9 most likely.

content.description: Biggest formation seen from the End of the Road in West Cochise.Roughly the size of the sheepshead, this dome has a lot to offer for those looking to expand their views and routes in the Stronghold. Climbed in the 60s or 70s by old skool climbers ( unknown). The original route goes up the middle of the formation and to the vegetated ledges and up the “Thumb” where a Two Piton anchor can be found. This is a great route to go and explore as well and it goes at around .10.
